race.comment: ECLAIR VITALITY (5) knuckled down strongly to grab second when resuming here last month. Kept fresh with 34 days between runs and will appreciate the extra 100m. Expect him to drift back early and be saved for the final shot at them. SMASHING ACTION (9) was a brave all the way winner last time at Gawler. Backs up quickly and gets weight off with the 2kg claimer engaged. Has more to offer fourth-up and from the good draw, she's sure to be in this for a very long way. TAKING OMAHA (13) pulled up with excuses last time when dropping out the back of the screen as favourite at Gawler. Freshened with 32 days and keeps Holder engaged. No shock to see him bounce back sharply. Have to keep safe. RUNAWAY BELLE (11) returns, readied with two trials. Lacks early toe but will appreciate the hot tempo, so she can launch late.
